      "test_name_raw": "subprocess_without_shell_equals_true",
      "judge_verdict": "UNCERTAIN",
      "judge_reason": "subprocess.run is called with a list (no shell=True), which prevents shell injection. However, the image and cmd values come from user-controlled JSON and are only validated with a regex (image) and a simple metacharacter check (cmd). The regex allows valid Docker images but does not prevent injection into the Docker daemon (e.g., via image name with '--' flags). The cmd check is weak (only ';' and '&' are blocked; backticks, $(), |, etc. are not). Since the code does not use shell=True, the risk is low but not zero due to potential Docker argument injection."
    }
